- Used to set the global config value


1) export const ConfigContext = React.createContext();

createContext([object,function])

createContext([object,(obj)=>obj])

2) Wrap the component with provider so that any component below this wrapper can access this

const configValue={
    xyz:true
}

<ConfigContext.Provider value={configValue}>
 <div></div>
</ConfigContext.Provider>

3) In your app, import the context;

import React , {useState, useEffect, useContext} from "react";
import {ConfigContext} from './App';
const context = useContext(ConfigContext);

4) take the value from context
context.xyz===false 

